  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, we--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Which, which was sort of nondescript.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The weather was pleasant.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was spring.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think for a brief moment, I enjoyed youth, childhood, a little bit because there were no pressures on me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then we moved to Brussels.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, as a matter of fact, both in Spa and in Brussels, but particularly in Spa, our wonderful friends went back and forth between my family in Germany and ourselves.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On Sundays, they would come and visit.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they would report on what was going on with the family we left behind in detail.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was through that very-- they had a very sad mission, because they came to tell us that my Uncle Carl, who was the physician, had tried in vain to get to Israel, which was then Palestine, and saw absolutely no, no way out of-- and he was just not going to be around for deportation.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so on March 17 in 1940, he took his life in order to escape what would lay ahead.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They also, on these trips over, unbeknownst to me, brought valuable things, jewelry, from my relatives, my grandmother, and my aunt, and uncle, and so forth, in order to help us.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And later, as the story unfolds, my father, at very crucial moments, sold this jewelry in order to obtain passage.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I'll sort of get to that a little bit later.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But they were faithful.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They came.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they cheered us up, especially my mother, who tended to be very depressed, and as I said, kept us abreast of what the family was doing.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
